# Next.js App Router rules

- Use the App Router conventions: `app/page.tsx`, `app/layout.tsx`, `app/api/**/route.ts`.
- Prefer Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when state, effects, browser APIs, or event handlers are needed.
- Do not use `window`, `document`, `localStorage`, or browser-only APIs in Server Components.
- Keep pages thin. Move reusable UI to `components/` and reusable data to `content/` or `lib/`.
- Use the Next.js Metadata API for titles, descriptions, Open Graph, canonical URLs, and robots settings.
- Use `next/image` for images and `next/font` for fonts when possible.
- Keep route handlers server-only. Validate all request data before using it.
- Do not mix unrelated concerns in a page file. Split sections into dedicated components.
- Avoid unnecessary client-side JavaScript for static landing sections.
